WEBVTT

00:00:00.240 --> 00:00:09.947
Good morning family, how are y'all doing today? Well, praise the Lord, I have Diana with me again and we are just excited to be here.

00:00:09.947 --> 00:00:17.265
You know, we're just seeking the Lord together and we've been reading this book by John Bevere, 'Drawing Near'.

00:00:17.266 --> 00:00:30.685
Yeah, it's amazing and it is phenomenal. We were just like scavengers, folks; we will look through wherever we can to find a good meal with the Lord.

00:00:30.686 --> 00:00:38.037
You know, if you don't feel like you're getting spiritually fed all the time in certain areas, you've got to find what it is.

00:00:38.038 --> 00:00:43.960
You can't just be lazy; you can't just depend on your pastor to feed you all the time.

00:00:43.961 --> 00:00:51.418
You've got to be bold enough and strong enough to go out there and say, 'Listen, I'm going to find me something today, whatever I need in my life.'Does that make sense?

00:00:51.419 --> 00:00:56.082
Yeah, not just on Wednesdays and Sundays—every day. Find something.

00:00:56.083 --> 00:01:03.438
You get your food on Sunday, you get your food on Wednesday, and if that's all you feed your spirit, your flesh eats every day, three times a day.

00:01:03.439 --> 00:01:11.506
If you feed your flesh two and three times a day, you need to feed your spirit, and you can't just feed it on Wednesdays and Sundays, right?

00:01:11.507 --> 00:01:17.267
So, Diana and I, we're always looking all the time for words that will fan the flame.

00:01:17.268 --> 00:01:28.159
How do you keep strong in these dark times? We had an election, and thank God it's over, but it's time to move on.

00:01:28.160 --> 00:01:36.152
I really believe the Holy Spirit is telling me, 'Brandon, let's not talk about politics no more.

00:01:36.153 --> 00:01:42.588
We're done.'We saw it, we had it, and the caravan's moving on, folks.

00:01:42.589 --> 00:01:48.340
I just can't park there no more; you'll dry up spiritually. Always praying for the election, always that stuff.

00:01:48.341 --> 00:01:55.118
Yeah, we pray for our government, we pray for our leaders, but we've got to get deeper in the things of God.

00:01:55.119 --> 00:02:13.916
I noticed even with this, I did my mission, I did what He said to do, and now He's telling me, 'Brandon, it's time for you to tell my people something different here.'Like we say, we came, we conquered; it's time to keep climbing.

00:02:13.917 --> 00:02:28.147
We don't build a tent there; we're climbers. So it's time to keep climbing, keep on pressing on. We've got to go to the summit, and I'm excited, y'all.

00:02:28.148 --> 00:02:48.479
You know, the Lord was instructing me about prayer, and He was talking about staying full, being filled and controlled by the Holy Spirit, but showing me examples of people who fake it a lot.

00:02:48.480 --> 00:03:04.513
You can fake being full for a season, for a little bit, and fool people because you have all the Christian lingo, the verbiage, the hallelujahs, the shouts, and you shake a little bit.

00:03:04.514 --> 00:03:08.951
You can put on a performance sometimes, and people fall for it.

00:03:08.952 --> 00:03:16.982
But if you're a seasoned veteran and you're watching that, you know the difference between fake and real.

00:03:16.983 --> 00:03:28.386
You know the difference between cold and hot, even whenever they pretend they're hot. You know when they start praying if there's no well there.

00:03:28.387 --> 00:03:37.318
I heard another person stand up before and they start praying, and the glory comes into the atmosphere.

00:03:37.319 --> 00:03:46.469
You can't mock the glory. When the glory is there, there's no flesh that can make that happen.

00:03:46.470 --> 00:03:51.719
It's beautiful when the spirit of the Lord comes in through prayer.

00:03:51.720 --> 00:04:00.801
It's Holy Ghost prayer versus somebody who is dry, trying to make prayer happen like a counterfeit.

00:04:00.802 --> 00:04:07.638
That's why we don't want that on our channel. I don't want to waste your time. If I don't feel it...

00:04:07.639 --> 00:04:16.085
there are some days I come here and I feel dry and I just try to get through, but I don't want that.

00:04:16.086 --> 00:04:28.879
I want to be filled with and controlled by the Holy Spirit so that when you take time out of your day, you're getting a fresh touch from the Holy Spirit.

00:04:28.880 --> 00:04:38.262
You walk away changed. I don't want to fall out in the Holy Ghost, shake a couple of times on the floor, and get up and be the same.

00:04:38.263 --> 00:04:43.136
No, I want impartation. I want to change. I want to go from glory to glory.

00:04:43.137 --> 00:05:11.576
I don't want to play church where we say a couple of whatever and we get up and we shake around and have a 'Holy Ghost thing'trying to mock what we had 10 years ago when we were kids.

00:05:11.577 --> 00:05:17.452
The Holy Spirit wasn't in it; it's just flesh. People get weird.

00:05:17.452 --> 00:05:25.813
I want something tangible, something I can bite my teeth into spiritually that's going to change me and draw me closer to Him.

00:05:25.814 --> 00:05:32.561
When we found this book by John Bevere, 'Drawing Near', it's exactly what we needed.

00:05:32.562 --> 00:05:47.348
He didn't sponsor this; we don't even know this man. We truly believe there's something in this.

00:05:47.349 --> 00:05:56.099
We've read a lot of his books and they're life-changing, very anointed.

00:05:56.100 --> 00:06:04.733
Some people say, 'Well, this is old,'but I don't care how old it is. I'm extremely picky about what I read.

00:06:04.734 --> 00:06:20.046
Diana will read a couple of pages and she'll go, 'This is trash,'and throw it away. A lot of people send us books and she'll throw them away.

00:06:20.047 --> 00:06:47.255
If you don't want to have your feelings hurt, don't tell her to read your book because we're not going to sugarcoat it. You can't counterfeit the Holy Spirit.

00:06:47.256 --> 00:06:55.569
We're veterans, folks, and I'm not trying to be prideful, but I'm a veteran when it comes to knowing what's real and authentic.

00:06:55.570 --> 00:07:05.316
I know it instantaneously. I'm like a tractor beam. I just know when you know.

00:07:05.317 --> 00:07:26.472
Even when you see people behind the pulpit, you listen to them and go, 'You just need to sit down.'I'm not trying to be rude, but you're wasting people's time if you didn't take the time to fill yourself up with the Holy Ghost before you came to church.

00:07:26.473 --> 00:07:50.798
Sit down and pass the baton to somebody else. I want to go from glory to glory.

00:07:50.799 --> 00:08:01.013
We get all caught up in the politics and everything going on and we camp there, but God's wanting to move the caravan and go up the mountain now.

00:08:01.014 --> 00:08:12.318
We've got to pray for this nation, yes, but we've got to get a harvest for the Kingdom; He is the Lord of the harvest.

00:08:12.319 --> 00:08:26.765
You can always tell when a book is written for money or if it's really Holy Spirit inspired.

00:08:26.766 --> 00:08:32.845
I don't want to cut you off, Diana, I'm sorry; I start rattling too much.

00:08:32.846 --> 00:08:50.825
I want you to show them, babe. This is what changes you. Aren't you ready for some authentic, quit-playing-church folks?

00:08:50.826 --> 00:09:00.398
I'm tired of walking away and not having a life-experience change with the Lord.

00:09:00.399 --> 00:09:26.398
I don't want to just fall down and shake a little bit; I want to get up and go, 'My God, I'm changed.'You get lackadaisical and comfortable as you're praying for the election and all that stuff, but you always have to come back to the heartbeat of God.

00:09:26.399 --> 00:09:44.139
What is He saying about this generation? Draw near. I'm desperate for a touch today.

00:09:44.140 --> 00:09:50.437
I see the emails and you're so broken; you're not getting fed at your churches.

00:09:50.438 --> 00:10:16.933
You're desperate for change, for your marriages, for healing, for all this stuff, but you're not going to the Source. It's about drawing near to Him. It's being like Moses.

00:10:16.934 --> 00:10:28.822
He had everything in Egypt, just like John Bevere talks about in his book, and he never once complained about wanting to go back.

00:10:28.823 --> 00:10:38.278
He even said, 'I don't want to go to the Promised Land, I don't want to go to the next level, if You're not going with us.

00:10:38.279 --> 00:11:23.404
I would rather stay here in the desert if I don't have You.'He chose the desert just to stay with God. That's desperate, because the desert is not a fun place.

00:11:23.405 --> 00:11:49.482
I don't think a lot of people want to go through any hard times—a financial collapse or any craziness—because anytime I bring it up, people say, 'Oh my God, I rebuke that.'But the Lord said to keep doing the same thing and asking for something different is insanity.

00:11:49.483 --> 00:12:02.559
We want change, we want the glory, we want revival. I had a mega-minister text me tonight asking, 'Where's the glory?

00:12:02.560 --> 00:12:18.179
Why haven't we seen it? What's the hold-up?'That's a great question.

00:12:18.180 --> 00:12:42.348
Where is the revival? Where is the presence of the Lord in the churches? Do you know of anything real happening?

00:12:42.349 --> 00:12:50.631
We had something at the tent revival a couple of weeks ago, but I haven't heard of anything since we focused on the election.

00:12:50.632 --> 00:12:57.812
We got what we wanted, and now we have the ability to turn around, but we don't want to change.

00:12:57.813 --> 00:13:07.630
They don't want to let go of their seeker-friendly message with skinny jeans and fog machines. They're like Moses's people—they choose to stay back.

00:13:07.631 --> 00:13:29.719
Moses went up on the mountain for 40 days, and they all had the ability to come up with him; the Lord invited every single one of them to have a relationship with Him.

00:13:29.720 --> 00:13:43.439
But they chose to send Moses because it was uncomfortable to their flesh. Aaron didn't go.

00:13:43.440 --> 00:13:58.205
Joshua had more fear of the Lord; he stood down there, wanting to be as close as he could.

00:13:58.206 --> 00:14:24.732
In Exodus, it says He drew them all there to have a relationship with Him. He's doing the same thing today.

00:14:24.733 --> 00:14:43.208
He's no respecter of persons; He wants a relationship with every single one of you.

00:14:43.209 --> 00:15:09.424
We are like sponges, folks. What you feed on the most is what's going to come out of you.

00:15:09.425 --> 00:15:18.347
I can tell a lot of times when we go around people, they don't have any Holy Ghost because they avoid the conversation.

00:15:18.348 --> 00:15:22.624
An exchange takes place over meals that is greater than in any other setting.

00:15:22.625 --> 00:15:31.113
This is why Paul tells us not to eat with someone who claims to be a believer yet lives in habitual sin—that's 1 Corinthians 5:11.

00:15:31.114 --> 00:16:10.113
We open our heart and become intimate over a meal. When people invite us out and get offended when we say no, it's not that I'm better than them; it's in 1 Corinthians. Diana, read that scripture.

00:16:10.114 --> 00:16:22.254
'But now I am writing to you that you must not associate with anyone who claims to be a brother or sister but is sexually immoral or greedy, an idolator or slanderer, a drunkard or swindler.

00:16:22.255 --> 00:16:35.043
Do not even eat with such people.'You've got to come up higher; be careful who you eat with.

00:16:35.044 --> 00:16:50.002
Jesus would go out and hang out with people, but He dominated the atmosphere.

00:16:50.003 --> 00:17:01.497
If you're not strong enough to dominate the atmosphere, don't hang around them because they'll influence you.

00:17:01.498 --> 00:17:39.557
You need to change atmospheres. I can feel the atmosphere through discernment and words of knowledge.

00:17:39.558 --> 00:18:37.574
I know if a pastor is dry or lukewarm. You can't fake it. We seek out where it's authentic. Here's another piece of the book I wanted her to read.

00:18:37.575 --> 00:19:35.019
The Holy Spirit told him to pull off the side of the road and whisper to his heart: 'Did I not say to you, pray without ceasing?'He responded, 'Yes Lord.'He probed further: 'Is prayer a monologue or dialogue?'He responded, 'It's a dialogue, Lord.'His words came quick: 'Well, if I said to pray without ceasing, then that means I am willing to communicate with you without ceasing.'The more you get to know a person, the more you learn their ways.

00:19:35.020 --> 00:20:21.558
It's the same with the Father. The more you draw near to Him, the more you know when something is bothering Him.

00:20:21.559 --> 00:21:37.846
I know when I've overstepped a line and need to apologize. I want to be quick to repent and follow the Holy Spirit.

00:21:37.847 --> 00:22:08.655
The Bible says He corrects those He loves. I want to grow. I don't want the next four years to be more of the same road.

00:22:08.656 --> 00:22:38.609
I'm ready for Him to come. But we have to have major changes. It might make your flesh squirm.

00:22:38.610 --> 00:23:09.872
People don't want a financial crisis, but the Lord is concerned about the unbeliever.

00:23:09.873 --> 00:23:35.544
What is it going to take to get the people in San Francisco, Portland, and Seattle to awaken? What draws them to repentance?

00:23:35.545 --> 00:24:27.927
Sometimes it takes a shake, like COVID did, to awaken the people in China or those who have cried out to Buddha or Muhammad and still don't have an answer.

00:24:27.928 --> 00:25:12.981
They need us to be the salt and light. The only way you'll get that is by drawing near.

00:25:12.982 --> 00:25:21.036
It's not politics; it's not Donald Trump; it's not the Senate or the House.

00:25:21.037 --> 00:25:37.317
The only thing that's going to change America is an awakening unto God.

00:25:37.318 --> 00:25:45.278
People get mad when I talk about a shaking, but I want what He wants.

00:25:45.279 --> 00:26:13.922
Jesus didn't want to die on the cross in His flesh; He sweat drops of blood, but He said, 'Not my will, but Yours be done.'What will it take to wake up the billions going to hell?

00:26:13.923 --> 00:27:11.116
They are comfortable in Las Vegas or the clubs. It's going to take something drastic.

00:27:11.117 --> 00:27:47.751
We're going to pray for the lost. I want revival and a harvest, but not at the expense of making our flesh comfortable.

00:27:47.752 --> 00:28:03.475
The glory comes with a price. Are you willing to pay it? It takes dying to self.

00:28:03.476 --> 00:29:04.403
The Lord even told Diana He's waiting on the harvesters. Tell them what the Lord told you, babe.

00:29:04.404 --> 00:29:17.468
'See, this is the problem with My body; they are so afraid of hearing the wrong voice that they don't even want to hear My voice at all, so they shut it all off.

00:29:17.469 --> 00:30:27.119
But if you're spending time in the word and seeking Me, you will hear it.'The enemy's goal is separation.

00:30:27.120 --> 00:30:35.825
People are afraid of the prayer language because they're stuck in their heads.

00:30:35.826 --> 00:31:38.676
If you spend time with Him and feed on the word, the rest will fall into place. If you can't hear God for yourself, you're in trouble.

00:31:38.677 --> 00:32:36.217
A seasoned person familiar with His voice doesn't have to test everything every single second because they know Him.

00:32:36.218 --> 00:33:45.057
It should always be backed by scripture. If I can't find it in the word, it ain't God.

00:33:45.058 --> 00:34:08.715
He's passionate about a relationship with you. Even the hang-up on Christmas—Jesus is the reason for the season.

00:34:08.716 --> 00:35:27.838
We celebrate Jesus. Some say Easter is pagan, too, but I celebrate anytime I can give God glory.

00:35:27.839 --> 00:35:33.380
We're not talking about some pagan entity; we're talking about 'Joy to the World'.

00:35:33.381 --> 00:36:35.688
I give gifts when the Lord says to. One year when we had nothing, someone gave us $1,000 for Christmas.

00:36:35.689 --> 00:36:58.691
People are so scared there's a devil behind every bush that they let people rob them of something joyous.

00:36:58.692 --> 00:37:14.047
If you don't want to follow the channel because I have a 'pagan tree', then bye.

00:37:14.048 --> 00:37:53.331
I'm determined to have a relationship with the Father. We seek deeper intimacy. I make an atmosphere for Him.

00:37:53.332 --> 00:38:15.157
If He showed up at your house, would He want to stay, or is there so much strife and crap?

00:38:15.158 --> 00:38:49.546
We're trying to fan your flame. We want to inspire you to be on fire.

00:38:49.547 --> 00:40:00.159
We see the emails and have compassion. I feel like I'm in an emergency ward.

00:40:00.160 --> 00:40:08.368
You're on spiritual life support and you need living water.

00:40:08.369 --> 00:41:35.922
Diana, read about the sand. His thoughts about you outnumber the grains of sand.

00:41:35.923 --> 00:43:34.910
Our value is determined by the purchaser. What is our value to God?

00:43:34.911 --> 00:43:43.846
That's where we find our true value. God sets the standard, not men.

00:43:43.847 --> 00:44:27.408
I encourage you to get the book; there are nuggets that will fan your flame. We pray for you. There is a great shaking coming.

00:44:27.409 --> 00:44:46.402
There will be days that seem dark, but there will be light in Goshen, folks, and we will have the greater glory.

00:44:46.403 --> 00:45:03.627
I told you there would be a reprieve, but when will the house of cards fall?

00:45:03.628 --> 00:45:34.669
There's too much debt; there has to be a reset. We're going to pray for the Lord to fan your flame.

00:45:34.670 --> 00:47:13.422
Father, we thank You for every person here. We call for a hunger to grow inside of them.

00:47:13.423 --> 00:48:00.972
We take authority over satanic forces and addictions. We thank You for a supernatural transfer.

00:48:00.973 --> 00:54:54.957
We thank You for books like this from John Bevere. We want to go from glory to glory.

00:54:54.958 --> 00:55:24.592
We lift up Elon Musk—this is day three—and we call him born again in the name of Jesus.

00:55:24.593 --> 00:55:30.920
According to Ephesians 1:18, let the eyes of his understanding be enlightened.

00:55:30.921 --> 00:55:56.849
Give him a supernatural encounter. Let him be the next Billy Graham. Let him use technology like Starlink for the gospel.

00:55:56.850 --> 00:57:02.620
We believe that for Elon Musk today, that he'll use that technology all for the glory of the living God, and Father, we believe it in Jesus'name.

00:57:02.621 --> 00:59:06.598
We love the good emails—like the one from the lady involved in the motorcycle accident.

00:59:06.599 --> 01:00:08.640
It's an honor that you watch. We've made it 30 days. God bless you all. Bye-bye.

